    <string name="introduction.steps.introduction">Introduction</string>
    <string name="introduction.steps.introduction.primary">Hi !\n\n

        This was a simple app made for myself because I managed to lose my phone multiple times, and I don\'t always have the cellular network thingy on.
        If you are like this or straight up don\'t want to use any Google services, this is for you !\n\n

        This app needs to be installed on 2 or more phones, or it will become useless.
    </string>
    <string name="introduction.steps.introduction.how_does_this_work">How does this work ?</string>
    <string name="introduction.steps.introduction.how_does_this_work_content">First of all you select a password (aka a private key),
        add new contacts and from there you can send actions to them (they need to have this app installed)\n
        For it to actually work, you need to add YOUR contact on the other phone and from there, actions will get sent through if enabled.\n\n

        Once configured, if you send actions it will get sent through as an SMS instead of relying on any external server.\n
        The data that\'s sent is encrypted.
    </string>
